OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781671666
OL,3,CStreeting prepared to trigger
OL,4,Cleadership contest as early as next
OL,5,Cweek
OL,7,FWes Streeting indicated he is prepared
OL,8,Fto trigger a Labour leadership contest
OL,9,Fas early as next week as he urged Sir
OL,10,FKeir Starmer to set out a timetable
OL,11,Ffor his departure if Andy Burnham wins
OL,12,Fthis week's Makerfield by-election.
OL,14,FThe former health secretary insisted
OL,15,Fhe has the backing of the 80 MPs
OL,16,Frequired to stand in a contest as he
OL,17,Faccused Sir Keir of not listening to
OL,18,Fthe party or his Cabinet in a series
OL,19,Fof public appearances on Tuesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781671666
OL,3,CStreeting prepared to trigger
OL,4,Cleadership contest as early as next
OL,5,Cweek
OL,7,FMeanwhile, the Prime Minister said he
OL,8,Fwould prove his rivals wrong and
OL,9,F"carry on with what I was elected to
OL,10,Fdo" and "bring back the change that
OL,11,Fpeople desperately need" as he fights
OL,12,Ffor his political future.
OL,14,FMr Streeting said he wanted Sir Keir
OL,15,Fto reflect over the weekend and make a
OL,16,Fdecision to leave "on his own terms"
OL,17,Fafter the June 18 vote which could see
OL,18,FMr Burnham return to Westminster to
OL,19,Fchallenge the Prime Minister.
OL,26,@qD@AOUrD@CO]rD@IOUsD@XO]xD@SOUxD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781671666
OL,3,CStreeting prepared to trigger
OL,4,Cleadership contest as early as next
OL,5,Cweek
OL,7,FBut pressed on whether he would
OL,8,Ftrigger a contest if Sir Keir stayed
OL,9,Fput, as the Prime Minister has made
OL,10,Fclear he wants to, the ex-Cabinet
OL,11,Fminister told BBC Newsnight: "We can't
OL,12,Fcarry on with this uncertainty and
OL,13,Fparalysis, and there will need to be a
OL,14,Fcontest, and I'd be prepared to do
OL,15,Fthat."
OL,26,@sD@^OUwD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781671666
OL,3,CStreeting prepared to trigger
OL,4,Cleadership contest as early as next
OL,5,Cweek
OL,7,FOn how soon he would be willing to
OL,8,Fmount a challenge, Mr Streeting said
OL,9,Fhe did not want to "get into, 'is it
OL,10,FMonday, is it Tuesday'", but that Sir
OL,11,FKeir should be given "space over the
OL,12,Fweekend" to consider his position.
OL,14,FAsked if he would challenge Sir Keir
OL,15,Fif the Greater Manchester Mayor does
OL,16,Fnot win the Makerfield by-election, he
OL,17,Ftold LBC's Andrew Marr show: "Yes, I
OL,18,Fbelieve we need a change of leadership
OL,19,Fand if Andy Burnham isn't back, I
OL,20,Fstill believe we need that change of
OL,21,Fleadership."
OL,26,@qD@TOUrD@WO]sD@VOUtD@HO]yD@^OU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
